{"comments":"Color Dynamics Types — ADTs for color source and variation control.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nColor dynamics control how brush color changes during a stroke. Unlike\nstatic color, dynamic color responds to input (pressure, tilt, time) or\nvaries randomly per dab. This creates rich, expressive marks that evoke\ntraditional media where pigment naturally varies.\n\n## Color Source\n\nWhere does the brush get its color?\n\n- **Foreground**: Single selected color (most common)\n- **Background**: Secondary color\n- **ForegroundBackground**: Blend between FG and BG based on input\n- **Gradient**: Sample from a gradient spectrum\n- **ColorSet**: Random selection from a palette\n- **Canvas**: Pick up color from existing paint (wet mixing)\n- **Image**: Sample from a reference image\n\n## Application Timing\n\nWhen does color change?\n\n- **PerStroke**: Color set once at stroke start\n- **PerDab**: Each dab gets fresh randomization\n- **Continuous**: Smooth interpolation along stroke\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[112,20],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Types.purs","start":[112,3]},"title":"ForegroundColor"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[113,20],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Types.purs","start":[113,3]},"title":"BackgroundColor"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[114,25],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Types.purs","start":[114,3]},"title":"ForegroundBackground"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[115,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/ColorDynamics/Types.purs","start":[115,3]},"title":"GradientSource"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataC